To address the "Missing or insufficient permissions" error when saving generated content, we need to ensure the user is authenticated with Firebase. Even though the application handles user profiles locally or via Google OAuth (client-side), Firebase Firestore requires a valid Firebase session (even an anonymous one) to allow writes under standard security rules.

I will update `App.tsx` to sign the user in anonymously to Firebase when they log in to the app. I will also update `services/contentService.ts` to verify authentication before attempting to save, preventing the error from crashing the experience.

